[thinking] **Understanding writeObject behavior**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm realizing that the custom writeObject method doesn't call the defaultWriteObject method. This means that it won't include field values in the stream, only the optional data, which consists of four BigInteger objects and attrCarrier data, followed by TC_ENDBLOCKDATA. I need to keep this in mind for how I manage data serialization. It's important to note this distinction, as it affects what gets stored in the stream!
